        "Minor in Social Media Content & Strategies": [
            "Minor in Social Media Content & Strategies The Minor in Social Media Content & Strategies introduces students to the fundamentals of strategic social media use, including how to create content that drives traffic to the site and helps organizations meet their goals. The four required courses provide an overview of strategy, copywriting, and analytics, including a special course to develop digital messaging. Two elective courses allow students to explore courses from across the Ric Edelman College of Communication, Humanities, & Social Sciences to build a minor that suits their academic preferences."
        ],
